Calculate additional variables related to body weight for cardiopulmonary exercise testing data

Source: R/add_weight.R
add_weight.Rd

add_weight() amplifies existing spiroergometric data by the calculation of body weight-related variables.

Usage

add_weight(data, weight = NULL)

Arguments

data

A data.frame of the class spiro containing the gas exchange data. Usually the output of a spiro call.

weight

A numeric value to manually set the participant's body weight.

Value

A data.frame of the class spiro containing the cardiopulmonary exercise testing data including variables relative to body weight.

Details

Based on the participant's body weight relative oxygen uptake (VO2_rel) and carbon dioxide (VCO2_rel) output are calculated. weight will be received from the original file's meta data, but can be manually overridden, e.g. if the value in the meta data is incorrect or rounded.

For running protocols, running economy (RE) is calculated.

# get example file
file <- spiro_example("zan_gxt")

s <- spiro(file)
add_weight(s, weight = 65.3)
